# Kendo UI Fluent Patterns

## Always Use VDC Wrappers in Mockups

```html
<!-- Use VDC wrapper -->
<vdc-button variant="primary">Save</vdc-button>
<vdc-grid [data]="items"></vdc-grid>

<!-- Don't use raw Kendo directly in mockups -->
```

## VDC Wrapper Pattern

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'vdc-button',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [ButtonsModule],
  template: `<button kendoButton [themeColor]="themeColor"><ng-content></ng-content></button>`
})
export class VdcButtonComponent {
  @Input() variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'destructive' = 'primary';
}
```

## Tailwind + Kendo Coexistence

- Use Tailwind for layout (flex, grid, spacing, positioning)
- Use Kendo theme for component styling (colors, borders, shadows)
- Override Kendo only via `_kendo-fluent-overrides.scss`

```html
<!-- Layout with Tailwind, component is Kendo -->
<div class="flex gap-4 p-6">
  <vdc-dropdown [data]="options"></vdc-dropdown>
  <vdc-button variant="primary">Apply</vdc-button>
</div>
```

## Focus Ring Styling

VDC uses a subtle semi-transparent blue focus ring instead of the default black Fluent theme focus ring.

### Global Configuration

Focus ring is configured in `_kendo-fluent-overrides.scss`:

| Property | Value | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| Color | `rgba(15, 108, 189, 0.5)` | 50% opacity primary blue |
| Width | `2px` | Ring thickness |
| Offset | `2px` | Gap between element and ring |

### Required CSS for Focus Override

When overriding Kendo component styles, ALWAYS include focus ring styling:

```scss
.k-button:focus,
.k-button.k-focus {
  outline: 2px solid rgba(15, 108, 189, 0.5);
  outline-offset: 2px;
  box-shadow: none;  // IMPORTANT: removes Kendo's black shadow
}
```

### Dark/Colored Backgrounds

For buttons on dark or colored backgrounds (like side nav rail), use white:

```scss
.dark-bg .k-button:focus {
  outline: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  outline-offset: 2px;
  box-shadow: none;
}
```

### What NOT to Do

```scss
// BAD: Removes focus indicator entirely - breaks accessibility
.k-button:focus {
  outline: none;
}

// BAD: Missing box-shadow removal - leaves black border
.k-button:focus {
  outline: 2px solid blue;
  // Forgot box-shadow: none!
}
```

### Components That Need Focus Styling

| Component | Selector | Notes |
|-----------|----------|-------|
| Buttons | `.k-button` | Most common |
| Chips | `.k-chip` | Filter pills |
| Inputs | `.k-input`, `.k-textbox` | Use border color change |
| Dropdowns | `.k-dropdown` | Use border color change |
